TextKor: “경고. \n이 게임에 등장하는 모든 인물 및 이름은 허구입니다만 실제로 일어난 사건 사고를 바탕으로 제작된 부분이 있습니다. 또한 정신적 가정폭력에 대한 묘사가 포함되어 있으므로 유의바랍니다. ”
TextEng: Warning. \nThough every characters and their names are fictional, some portion of the events that transpire in the game were based on real crimes. This game also contains violence and coarse language. Viewer discretion is advised.

TextKor: “안전 불감증 : 모든 것이 안전할거라고 생각하며 위험은 없다고 생각하는 사람들에게 나타는 증상”
TextEng: “A false sense of security : A belief that you are safe when you are not”

TextKor: “안전 불감증 : 모든 것이 안전할거라고 생각하며 위험은 없다고 생각하는 사람들에게 나타는 증상”
TextEng: “A false sense of security : A belief that you are safe when you are not”
“Ugh... it's been a while since I had a sour stomach. I should've known I was overdrinking...”
“Gotta take a shower... before... drifting off... ”
“...What time is it? How long was I asleep? ”

TextKor: “시계가 안 보이는데… 폰은 또 어디 있는 거지?”
TextEng: “I can't see the clock on the wall... Where did I leave my phone again?”
“...Did I leave my guitar case there?”
“But I always keep the case near that wall--”
“What's this... I have two of them? ”

TextKor: “아, 씨… 잘못 가져왔나? 저거 누구 거지? 시온이 건가? ”
TextEng: “Ugh, for god's sake... did I accidentally take someone else's? Whose is that? Is it Sion's?”

TextKor: “잘 안 보이네… 어딘가 스티커가 붙어있을 텐데. ”
TextEng: “I can't really tell... there should be a sticker somewhere. ”
“...Hold on... That's not a case, it's...”

TextKor: “(뭔가 기분 나쁜 꿈을 꾼 것 같은데…)”
TextEng: “(I can't remember, but I'm pretty sure I had a nightmare...)”

TextKor: “(진짜 술 좀 작작 먹어야지, 이딴 일도 생기네. )”
TextEng: “(That's new. I need to stop drinking so much.)”

TextKor: “(오전 8시 밖에 안 됐네. 꿈자리가 뒤숭숭해서 그런지 좀 일찍 깼어.)”
TextEng: “(It's only 8 AM. I must have woken up early because of the nightmare..)”

TextKor: “(이제 기말 기간이니까 오늘은 그래도 공부 좀 해둬야지.)”
TextEng: “(Final's right around the corner, I'd better stay home and study today.)”
“No, I don't recall making that promise. ”
“I'm serious, what are you f*cking on about?”
“WHY ARE YOU TELLING ME THIS SO LATE?!”

TextKor: “미치겠네, 빨래 좀 제때 해둘 걸. 입을 게 없어. ”
TextEng: “Dammit, I should've done the laundry. I got nothing to wear. ”

TextKor: “(적어도 유나는 내가 집으로 데려다주고 왔으니 안심이지만. )”
TextEng: “(At least I got to take Yuna back to her home, which I'm happy with.)”
“(I gotta catch up with other subjects, the final's right around the corner. )”
“(But I'm in a bad shape, so I'll just start tomorrow.)”
“(...Did I leave the door open all day?)”
“The cops are on their way, so you'd better scram before I count to 3. ”
“(I'll definitely hop into shower before bed tonight.)”
“(Dammit, I left my phone at the bar!!)”

TextKor: “(어쩔 수 없지, 경찰서로 직접 뛰어가는 수 밖에!)”
TextEng: “(I guess there's no choice other than to run to the station!)”

TextKor: ““지난 29일 20대 남성 김 모 씨가 다섯 번의 전과가 있는 58세 이 모 씨의 손에 살해당했습니다. ”
TextEng: ““A young man in his 20's, Kim, was killed in the hands of a man of 58, Lee, who previously had 5 crime records. ”

TextKor: “이 모 씨는 밤 10시 경 김 모 씨의 거주지에 침입했습니다. ”
TextEng: “Kim hadn't noticed his door was left unlocked as he was leaving, ”

TextKor: “김 모 씨가 오후에 외출하면서 현관문을 제대로 닫지 않은 틈을 이용한 겁니다. ”
TextEng: “and Lee took advantage of that to sneak in at 10PM. ”

TextKor: “들어간 직후 복도에서 김 모 씨의 발 소리가 들려, ”
TextEng: “As he heard Kim's footsteps coming from the corridor, ”

TextKor: “화장실 문 뒤에 숨어있다가 피해자의 뒤를 쫓아…””
TextEng: “he hid behind the bathroom door, and chased after the victim...“”
“What a scary world we live in, right?”

TextKor: “요새는 혼자 사는 것만큼 위험한 게 없어요. 다들 누군가와는 같이 살어야 돼.”
TextEng: “Nothing's more dangerous than living alone these days. Everyone should have someone else to be with at home. ”

TextKor: “거, 처자도 가면 같이 살 사람 있죠? ”
TextEng: “Say, you have someone to live with in your new home, right?”

TextKor: “이 아저씨도 딸이 있는데 요번에 결혼해서 같이 살 사람이 생겼거든. ”
TextEng: “This ol' man has a daughter too. She recently got married, so she'll live with her husband from now on. ”

TextKor: “아마 딸 가진 아버지들은 다 똑같이 걱정이 태산일 거요. ”
TextEng: “I swear, all the fathers with daughters are the same; they worry day and night. ”
“Yikes, not in a dangerous world like this. ”
“You should call your parents often, they'd be worried sick about you. ”

TextKor: “당신은 입꼬리를 말려 올리곤 창 밖을 바라본다. ”
TextEng: “You curl the corners of your lips and stare out the window. ”

TextKor: “졸음이 몰려온다. 눈을 깜빡일 때마다 풍경이 바뀐다. ”
TextEng: “You get drowsy. What you see outside changes everytime you blink. ”
“From a forest to the inside of the tunnel, from the tunnel to the farm. ”

TextKor: “어… 내가 맘 같아서는, 문 앞까지 따악 갖다 주고 싶은데, ”
TextEng: “Hmm... I'd love to bring all your belongings right to your door, but, ”

TextKor: “문이 이렇게 따닥따닥 붙어있어서야 둘 데가 없네. 아마 이웃들이 뭐라 할 거여. ”
TextEng: “The doors to the other rooms are packed together, the boxes will get in the way of the other tenants. They'll probably complain. ”

TextKor: “더 기다리면 다음 일에 늦어서 지금 가봐야 되는디. ”
TextEng: “I can't wait any longer or I'll be late for my next work. ”

TextKor: “미안하지만, 나중에 집주인 분 오시면 도와달라 그래요. ”
TextEng: “Sorry to be saying this, but I think you should ask your landlord to help you out when they come. ”

TextKor: “아이고 학생~! 늦어서 미안해 정말. 혹시 어디야? ”
TextEng: “My, I'm real sorry for being late, darling! Where are you right now?”
“Hi, hello! You're the one who rented room 105, right? ”

TextKor: “아유, 미안해. 팔이 이러니까 혼자 아무것도 못 하겠더라고. ”
TextEng: “Again, sorry for being late, I couldn't do anything well with my arm like this. ”

TextKor: “근데 진짜 운 좋다. 딱 비자마자 계약해서 바로 들어오게 됐네. ”
TextEng: “I have to say, you got pretty lucky! You rented this room right after it became available. ”
“Now, let's head on into the room. ”

TextKor: “아, 비밀번호 알려줄게. 나중에 집에 들어가면 학생이 바꿔? ”
TextEng: “Oh, I should tell you the password. You change it on your own when you get in, okay? ”

TextKor: “아유, 나 때문에 이삿짐이 죄다, 저 뭐야, 로비에 있네. ”
TextEng: “Aw, man. Looks like all your stuff are in the uh... the lobby because I came too late. ”

TextKor: “어제 집주인 아저씨랑 미리 청소 깨ㅡ끗이 해뒀으니까, 학생은 짐만 옮겨오면 돼.”
TextEng: “My husband and I cleaned up the place, so all you gotta do is bring your stuff in. ”
“I'd love to help out, but I have a hospital appointment. ”
“If you have any questions, ask away!”
“They're near the stairs in the first floor. ”

TextKor: “아마 이번 일요일이면 고지서가 올 텐데 그건 예전 세입자가 정산했으니 무시해도 돼. ”
TextEng: “I think the bills will come in this Sunday, but that's already been payed for. Don't pay no mind to that. ”

TextKor: “그래도 주기적으로 확인하는 게 좋을 거야. 뭐가 올지 모르니까. ”
TextEng: “It's best you check it everyday though. You never know what you're going to miss. ”

TextKor: “어어… 요 앞에 보면 편의점도 있고, 식당도 좀 있고… ”
TextEng: “Hmm... there's a convenience store up front, some restaurants nearby... ”
“Oh, there's a police station as well. I doubt you'll ever go there, though. ”

TextKor: “아, 그거? 공지사항이나 세입자끼리 쪽지를 붙여두는 곳이야. ”
TextEng: “You noticed that? It's for me to post notices and for tenants to put up sticky notes. ”

TextKor: “원래는 화이트보드였는데, 누가 자꾸 마카를 가져가는 바람에 바꿨어. ”
TextEng: “We had to change from a whiteboard to the current one because some thief kept stealing the markers. ”

TextKor: “웬만한 분쟁은 내가 해결하고 싶지만, 워낙 멀리 사는데다가… ”
TextEng: “Usually I'd take care of the conflicts between tenants, but I live far away from here, and...”

TextKor: “서로 얼굴 보고 얘기하면 스트레스받는 일도 생긴대서 마련한 대책이지. ”
TextEng: “tenants didn't want to talk face-to-face with each other, so I came up with this solution. ”

TextKor: “하지만 문제를 일으킨 세입자가 밖에 나갈 일이 없으면, 문제가 아예 해결되지 않기도 해.”
TextEng: “But some tenants rarely leave their home and conflicts stay unresolved. ”

TextKor: “빨리 해결되길 바란다면, 차라리 문제가 있는 호수로 찾아가서 부탁하거나, 경찰에 민원을 넣는 편이 나을 거야. ”
TextEng: “So if you want problems settled posthaste, it might be better to walk up and knock on their doors or just call the cops. ”

TextKor: “혹시 알아? 말만 예쁘게 해도 잘 해결 될지. ”
TextEng: “Who knows? Maybe being polite is the key. ”
“Oh, I guess you're too young to understand. ”

TextKor: “예전에는 4를 불운으로 여겨서 엘리베이터에도 4층 대신 F층이 있다거나, ”
TextEng: “Back in the days, number 4 was infamous for being a bad omen. ”
“Buttons for 4th floor in elevators were changed to “F“ floors, and the labels on the rooms skipped 4. ”

TextKor: “이 건물도 마찬가지인 거야. 다른 층도 4호는 없어. ”
TextEng: “This building was built in that era too; none of the floors have a room that ends with 4. ”

TextKor: “하지만 미신이야, 미신. 세상에 불운이라든가 귀신 같은 게 어딨겠어. ”
TextEng: “It's just a superstition, though. There's no such thing as ghosts. ”

TextKor: “박스는 가능한 빨리 치워줘. 게시판을 가리고 있으니까. ”
TextEng: “Oh, and please move the boxes in asap. It's covering the board. ”
“Call me if you have any problems.”

TextKor: “이제 짐을 옮겨야 한다. 당신은 현관문이 안 닫히게 고정해뒀다. ”
TextEng: “You have to move the boxes. You fixed the door open so it doesn't close when you're moving. ”
“...There should be 10, but one of them is missing. ”

TextKor: “이사 트럭에서 로비로 가져왔을 때는 분명히 개수가 맞았다. ”
TextEng: “You could've sworn there was the right amount when you brought them to the lobby. ”

TextKor: “당신은 혹시 모르니 다른 층도 살펴보기로 한다. ”
TextEng: “You decide to check on the other floors just in case. ”

TextKor: “SHIFT를 누른 채 이동하면 달릴 수 있다. ”

TextEng: “...The box is nowhere to be found. ”
“You didn't see any security cameras in the corridors. ”
“You wonder which of the many boxes went missing. ”
“You decide to go back to the room. ”
“I didn't mean to startle you, sorry. ”

TextKor: “그게... 택배가 자, 잘못 온 것 같은데, 주소가 여기라서요. ”
TextEng: “It's just that... I got a wrong package and the address says it's for here, so...”

TextKor: “오래 전에 지저분하게 뜯었던 운송장 번호 위에 악필로 세 자리의 숫자가 적혀있다. ”
TextEng: “Over the poorly torn transport document, you see a poorly scribbled number in three digits. ”
“Here, it's yours. Sorry for scaring you. ”

TextKor: “당신은 짐을 부치지 않고 트럭으로 옮겼기 때문에 새 주소를 적지 않았다. ”
TextEng: “You didn't write your new address because you moved all the boxes along with you. ”

TextKor: “…현관에 안전고리가 없다. 당신은 불안해졌다. 지금까지 살면서 이런 일이 없었기에 더욱. ”
TextEng: “You notice the door doesn't have any door chain. You felt anxious. More so after experiencing this. ”
“You need a door chain. But to install it, you need a drill. ”

TextKor: “한 번만 쓸 드릴을 비싼 돈 들여 사는 것보다는 집주인께 부탁하는 게 나을 것이다. ”
TextEng: “Asking the landlord for one may be a better option than wasting money on a tool you'd only use once. ”

TextKor: “설치는 해줄 수 있는데 물건은 학생이 사야 돼. ”
TextEng: “I can install it for you, but you'll have to buy it yourself. ”

TextKor: “여보, 내일 105호 가서 안전고리 설치해 줄 수 있어? ”
TextEng: “Honey, can you go install a security chain for room 105? ”

TextKor: “어, 밥 먹고 가면 3시 쯤 될 거라고? ”
“내일 오후 3시쯤 되실 거 같은데 어때, 시간 괜찮아? ”
TextEng: “My husband can visit there at 3PM, how's that sound? ”

TextKor: “어어, 그래 그럼 3시에 가시는 걸로 알고 있을게? ”
TextEng: “Alright then, I'll send him over at 3. ”
“The door chain will arrive tomorrow morning if you order it now through Shopin.”
“You can take out your phone by pressing [ESC]. ”
“You're running out of cash. It's time to get a new part-time job. ”

TextKor: “당신은 이제 짐도 다 풀었으니 씻기로 한다. ”
TextEng: “You decide to take a cold shower, now that you're done unpacking. ”

TextKor: “잊지 않기 위해 일기장에 적어두는 게 좋겠다. ”
TextEng: “Let's take a memo in your diary just in case. ”

TextKor: “전보다 나은 곳에 취직하고 싶다면 공부를 많이 해둬야 한다. ”
TextEng: “For a better workplace you'll need to study as hard as you can. ”
“The upcoming language test is due on the next month. ”

TextKor: “당신은 이곳의 생활에 대해 집주인 분께 어제 미리 여쭤봤다. ”
TextEng: “You already asked your landlord about everything yesterday. ”

TextKor: “알바는 월요일부터 시작이니 오늘은 원하는대로 하루를 보내기로 한다. ”
TextEng: “Your part-time job starts on Monday; you're free to do anything the whole day as you please. ”
“You have a job interview at 11 today. ”
“You need to head to the convenience store now. ”

TextKor: “편의점은 북쪽으로 세번째 교차로까지 간 후 왼쪽 길로 가면 있다. ”
TextEng: “Walking up north until the third crossroad and turning left will take you to the convenience store. ”
“You can always take a look at the map at the bus station if you're unsure. ”

TextKor: “면접이 끝났다. 결과는 오후 1시쯤에 받을 수 있다.”
TextEng: “You finished the interview. You'll hear back from them around 1PM. ”
“It's the security chain you ordered yesterday. ”
“The landlord's husband is visiting at 3PM to install door chains. ”
“You decide it's time to go back home. ”
“Yeah, I'm, uh, here to install your security chain. ”

TextKor: “이제 현관문과 상호작용해서 안전고리를 걸 수 있다. ”
TextEng: “You can now interact with the door to lock the chain. ”
“Oh? That's good for me, but what's with you today?”
“Stop asking questions and just gimme the thing you picked, she's waiting here you know. ”
“Hey, are you seeing someone right now?”
“Sorry, please don't mind him. Here's my card. ”

TextKor: “계산이 끝나자마자 얼굴이 새빨개진 학생이 다른 학생의 팔을 붙들고 도망쳐 나갔다. ”
TextEng: “The person who paid quickly jerked the other's arm and ran off, his face flushed with embarrassment.”

TextKor: “그리고 퇴근할 때가 되어서야 물건이 몇 개 사라졌다는 걸 알아차렸다. ”
TextEng: “And it was only when you were leaving work, that you discovered some things were stolen. ”
“It's alright, I'll take care of that. ”

TextKor: “아냐, 정말 괜찮아. 이런 일로 해고하진 않을 거야. ”
TextEng: “No, it's fine, really. I won't fire you for that. ”

TextKor: “그보다 알바 첫날부터 이런 일을 당하다니 충격이 크겠구나. ”
TextEng: “You must be in quite a shock, especially since today was your first day of work. ”
“Forget about what happened. Go home and rest well, okay? ”

TextKor: “당신은 뛰쳐나올 것 같은 심장을 뒤로하고 재빨리 블라인드를 쳤다. ”
TextEng: “You quickly shut the blinds as your heart tries to run out of your chest. ”
“But they arrived 40 minutes after the man ran away. ”

TextKor: “거 없어진지 40분이나 됐으면 연락해서 갔다고 말이라도 해주세요. ”
TextEng: “Why didn't you call us to tell us he's no longer here?”
“It took us a while to get here you know?”
“The customer shoves you the stuff they just bought.”

TextKor: “이거 1+1 상품이잖아. 방금 결제한 거 환불해줘. 하나만 가져갈래.”
TextEng: “It's a buy one get one free, yeah? I want to get a refund for the one I bought. I just need one, not two.”
“Oh, sweety. You're new to working here, aren't you?”
“This works, you know? Like, in other places as well? It's okay if you didn't know.”

TextKor: “아니, 왜 자꾸 안 된다고만 해? 딴데서는 됐다니까?”
TextEng: “I'm telling you, girl. They refunded for me in other stores.”

TextKor: “학생 이상하네? 여기 매니저야? 너 뭐 돼?”
TextEng: “You're so weird. Who are you to decide? You the manager here? ”
“Call your manager, kid. I want to have a conversation with an adult. ”

TextKor: “그거 안 되는 거 맞는데요? 어디서 됐는데요?”
TextEng: “She's right, though, that's not how it works. Where did you get a refund? ”
“What you're doing is illegal, is what I'm saying. ”
“Wh-what are you on about? I, I told dew, told you, it was fine last time!”

TextKor: “괜한 오지랖 부렸다가 개쪽당하지나 말고 빠져, 학생.”
TextEng: “Don't stick your nose into other people's business and butt out, boy. ”

TextKor: “아~ 그러세요? 그럼 누가 개쪽당하나 한 번 볼까요?”
TextEng: “Oh, that's some confidence you have, ma'am. Let's see about that, shall we? ”

TextKor: “어디 가지 마시고 여기 꼼짝말고 계세요, 경찰에 신고해볼테니까.”
TextEng: “Do not move an inch from where you are, I'm calling the fuzz. ”

TextKor: “어후, 말이 안 통하네. 똥이 더러워서 피하지 내가.”
TextEng: “UGH, it's like I'm talking to a wall. I'm leaving. ”
“Oh, I want you to have one; here. ”

TextKor: “저 손님 때문에 1+1 상품 볼 때마다 저 진상 생각나면 좀 그렇잖아요.”
TextEng: “It'd be awful to be reminded of that ol' lady everytime you stock up on these buy one get ones. ”

TextKor: “요새 날이 더워져서 그런지 평소보다 옷이 더 들러붙는다.”
TextEng: “You feel like your shirt is sticking to your body; it's likely due to the rising heat. ”
“You decide to take a quick shower. ”

TextKor: “왠지 예전에 비해 옷이 몇 장 없는 것 같은 기분이 든다. ”
TextEng: “It could be your imagination, but it feels like your clothes are missing. ”
“Someone's knocking the doors of every room in this floor. ”
“There wasn't any notification regarding the regular disinfection. ”
“Maybe they have something to do with pseudo religion. ”
“It'd be best to ignore them in that case. ”
“Where did you want me to go, then?”

TextKor: “…이 문은 방음이 좋지 않기에 건너편의 사람이 통화 중이면 전화를 받는 상대의 목소리도 들린다.”
TextEng: “...The door of this room is thin enough to let you hear everything when someone's on the other side on their phone. ”

TextKor: “하지만 이번엔 전화 받는 상대의 목소리가 들리지 않았다. ”
TextEng: “But you didn't hear anyone on the other side of the phone this time. ”

TextKor: “다름이 아니라, 어제 새로 생긴 식당에 가족이랑 갔었는데 맛있길래.”
TextEng: “I took my family out to a new restaurant yesterday and the food was great there, so.. ”

TextKor: “엄청 별 건 아니지만 직원들도 나눠주려고 왔어.”
TextEng: “I'm just here to give my employee some food. ”

TextKor: “OO씨만 주는 게 아니라 오후 담당 직원한테도 주는 거니까 부담갖지 말고 받아.”
TextEng: “Please feel free to accept it, as I've brought this for both you and the afternoon employee.”
“You received the warm food your manager brought. ”
“Your mouth waters from the delicious smell. ”

TextKor: “요새 안색이 좀 안 좋아보인다? 무슨 일 있니?”
TextEng: “You're not looking so well these days. Is something the matter? ”
“I see, the walls must be as thin as a sheet of paper. ”

TextKor: “그러고보니, 딸이 사놓고 안 쓰는 게 있는데.”
TextEng: “Now that I think about it, there's this thing my daughter bought and never used. ”

TextKor: “한번 물어보고 줘도 된다 그러면 내일 한 번 가져와볼 테니, 괜찮으면 가져가라.”
TextEng: “I'll ask her and see if I can give it to you, take it if you like it. ”
“No, it's alright. You remind me a lot of my own daughter, that's all. ”

TextKor: “나도 20대에 고시원 살아봐서 알아. 소음 스트레스 꽤 심하니까. 그리고…”
TextEng: “I used to live in this cramped up dorm with thin walls back in my 20's, it's real stressful. And...”

TextKor: “꽁으로 주는 게 아니라 더 열심히 일하라는 의미로 주는 거야.”
TextEng: “I'm not giving it to you for free, I'm giving it to you so you can work harder. ”

TextKor: “직원 컨디션이 좋아야 일도 잘 하지. 아파서 그만두면 나도 새로 채용하기 귀찮다.”
TextEng: “Your condition affects the work efficiency. It'd be more work for me if you quit due to health issues. ”

TextKor: “음식 싸둔 건 이따가 교대할 때 오후 직원한테도 하나 전해주고.”
TextEng: “Don't forget to give one of the paper bags to the afternoon shift, yeah?”
“Good luck with your remaining hours, see ya. ”

TextKor: “어어, OO씨. 이거, 어제 물어봐준다고 했던 거. ”
TextEng: “Hey. Here's the thing I talked about yesterday. ”
“You received a pair of soundproof earmuffs. ”
“You can only use this at home. ”

TextKor: “듣자하니 몇 번 썼다나봐. 완전 새 건 아니지만 쓸 만해.”
TextEng: “She said she used it a few times. It's not exactly brand new, but it's useable. ”

TextKor: “그래도 하루종일 쓰진 마, 귀에 박테리아 증식한대. ”
TextEng: “But don't wear it all day, your ears might grow too much bacteria. ”
“Did I sound like a boomer? Haha. ”

TextKor: “아무튼 종종 쓰면 스트레스 받는 일은 좀 줄어들 거야.”
TextEng: “Anyhow, wear this from time to time to lessen the amount of stress you gain. ”
“Not this, the one on the right. ”

TextKor: “이거 그림이 안 예쁘잖아. 딴 걸로 줘. ”
TextEng: “I don't like this picture. Gimme something else. ”
“You're dull as hell. How are you going to survive if you don't know how to work? ”
“Here, keep the change and get yourself something nice. ”
“...One of the coins says “In dog we trust“. ”

TextKor: “어, OO씨. 잠깐 뭐 좀 확인하려고 들렀어.”
TextEng: “Heya, I forgot to check on something in the store. ”

TextKor: “맞다, 어제 받은 음식 어땠어? 오후 담당 직원은 괜찮다고 하던데.”
TextEng: “Oh yeah, how was the food? The afternoon staff seemed to like it. ”

TextKor: “에휴… 동네에 뭐 이런 사람이 다 있냐. ”
TextEng: “Ugh... what kind of people are living in this town? ”
“It's okay, I'll take care of this. ”

TextKor: “아냐, 아냐. 다른 일도 숱하게 겪어봐서 어떻게 해야하는지는 내가 더 잘 알아.”
TextEng: “No, no. I've had worse happen, so I know better on what to do in this case. ”
“You decided to go straight to the police station. ”

TextKor: “이사 오고나서부터 아가씨 사는 집 우편함에 편지 봉투가 오는데.”
TextEng: “You kept getting these envelopes in your mail box ever since you moved in, ”

TextKor: “봉투에 발신 주소도, 우표도 없고. 안에 있는 건 덜랑 사진 한 장인데다.”
TextEng: “it didn't have any address, or a postal stamp. And it had a single photo inside every time. ”
“Then today you got a photo of yourself in it, correct? ”

TextKor: “그, 지문 감식은 해볼 수 있는데. 2주 정도 걸리는데다가요,”
TextEng: “We can, uh, try to find fingerprints on it, which it takes around two weeks. ”

TextKor: “아마 이렇게까지 했으면 처음부터 아무것도 안 나올 수도 있어요.”
TextEng: “But based on what they did so far, there could be no prints left on the photos in the first place. ”

TextKor: “건물에 CCTV가 없다고 하셨으니 잡기도 어려울 것 같은데.”
TextEng: “Your house doesn't even have security cams, so the chance of catching this person seems near impossible. ”
“just rip that photo into pieces and forget about it?”
“You feel threatened because of that, yeah?”

TextKor: “아니, 저희가 뭐 해드릴 수 있는 게 없다니까요?”
TextEng: “No, like, we can't really do anything about it though. ”
“Come back once you have some solid evidence, alright?”

TextKor: “이사 오고나서부터 아가씨 사는 집 우편함에 편지 봉투가 오는데.”
TextEng: “You kept getting these envelopes in your mail box ever since you moved in, ”

TextKor: “봉투에 발신 주소도, 우표도 없고. 안에 있는 건 덜랑 사진 한 장인데다.”
TextEng: “it didn't have any address, or a postal stamp. And it had a single photo inside every time. ”
“Then today you got a photo of yourself in it, correct? ”

TextKor: “그, 지문 감식은 해볼 수 있는데. 2주 정도 걸리는데다가요,”
TextEng: “We can, uh, try to find fingerprints on it, which it takes around two weeks. ”

TextKor: “아마 이렇게까지 했으면 처음부터 아무것도 안 나올 수도 있어요.”
TextEng: “But based on what they did so far, there could be no prints left on the photos in the first place. ”

TextKor: “건물에 CCTV가 없다고 하셨으니 잡기도 어려울 것 같은데.”
TextEng: “Your house doesn't even have security cams, so the chance of catching this person seems near impossible. ”
“just rip that photo into pieces and forget about it?”
“You feel threatened because of that, yeah?”

TextKor: “아니, 저희가 뭐 해드릴 수 있는 게 없다니까요?”
TextEng: “No, like, we can't really do anything about it though. ”
“Come back once you have some solid evidence, alright?”

TextKor: “사진과 함께 세이톡도 봐서는 스토킹으로 잡을 수 있을 것 같지만…”
TextEng: “With the photos and messages you received, we COULD see this as a case of stalking...”
“But unfortunately, we're not a 100% sure we can put him behind bars. ”
“It has to do with the law. ”

TextKor: “지금까지 이 사람한테 하지 말라거나 싫다는 표현을 직접적으로 하지 않으셔서, 거부 의사가 있었다고 보긴 어려워요.”
TextEng: “You never explicitly said no to this person, so it's hard to interpret this as refusal. ”

TextKor: “스토킹으로 신고하려면 싫다고 하신 후에도 이런 일이 반복되어야 해요.”
TextEng: “If you want to report this as a case of stalking, they'll have to continue sending you messages AFTER you reject them. ”

TextKor: “죄송하지만 저희가 해드릴 수 있는 게 없습니다.”
TextEng: “I'm sorry, we can't help you on this one. ”

TextKor: “이대로 가만히 있으면 어떤 일이 생길지 모른다. ”
TextEng: “You have to do something before you get into further trouble. ”

TextKor: “쇼팡에 품절되어 있던 CCTV와 SD카드 재고가 들어왔다.”
TextEng: “It looks like previously sold out items, CCTV and SD card, are now available. ”

TextKor: “이제 돈만 충분하면 사서 설치할 수 있을 것이다.”
TextEng: “You'll be able to get them installed once you have enough money. ”

TextKor: “…설치하는 방법이 조금 복잡해서 조금 더 공부해야할 것이다. ”
TextEng: “...You'll also have to study a bit more to fully understand how to install these by yourself. ”
“Something cuts through your finger as you turn on the door knob. ”
“You removed the razor from the door knob. ”

TextKor: “아, 아… 잘못 왔구나. 죄송해요. 여기 몇 호예요?”
TextEng: “Uh, oh... I'm at the wrong house. Sorry. Which room is this?”
“Wow, I can't believe someone's living here. ”

TextKor: “조심해요. 여기 살던 사람, 다 도망갔어요. 귀신 들렸다나?”
TextEng: “Be careful. Everyone who ever lived here ran away. They say it's haunted. ”

TextKor: “당신은 내일이 월요일이라 오늘 분리수거를 미리 해둬야한다는 걸 떠올렸다. ”
TextEng: “You remembered it's Monday tomorrow, which means you'll have to recycle today. ”

TextKor: “너도 이따 밥 먹고 분리수거 좀 해라. ”
TextEng: “You should put them up too once we finish lunch. ”

TextKor: “어허. 미리 좀 해봐야 나중에 누구랑 같이 살 때도 편한 거야.”
TextEng: “Come, now. It's good to practice in advance to make living with others easier.”
“Then why don't you join the three of us?”
“Mom's going to be off duty soon. ”

TextKor: “종강해서 애들도 다 올라가고 나 혼자 있기 심심해. ”
TextEng: “All my friends went back home, nobody's around the town. I'm bored. ”
“Don't worry about the money, dad's paying. ”

TextKor: “사주긴 할 건데 그걸 왜 니가 말하냐?”
TextEng: “I mean, I will, but that's not for you to decide. ”

TextKor: “당신은 화목한 모습을 보고 있자니 속이 이상해졌다. ”
TextEng: “Watching this happy family makes your stomach turn. ”
“Uh? What's wrong? Do you feel sick? ”

TextKor: “이런… 그럼 하는 수 없지. 다음에 사줄게.”
TextEng: “Well then, I'll buy you some other time. ”
“Go get some rest, and tell me if you want to call in sick tomorrow. ”
“You have no way to check if anything really moved, either. ”
“It's getting hot; you decide to take a shower. ”

TextKor: “대학은 가지 않았다. 정확히는 가지 못한 것이지만.”
TextEng: “You didn't go to college. Not that you had a choice, though. ”

TextKor: “혼자서는 도저히 등록금을 낼 형편이 되지 않았으며, 그렇다고 장학금을 탈 정도로 공부머리가 좋지도 못하다.”
TextEng: “You couldn't afford the tuition fee on your own. You weren't smart enough to get scolarship, either. ”
“So you concluded you'll need to be better at something than others. ”

TextKor: “대학이야 중요하지 않다지만, 빈번히 뜨는 불합격 문자를 보면 잘 모르겠다. ”
TextEng: “People say your diploma doesn't matter, but the frequent use of the word 'unfortunately' regarding your resume says otherwise. ”

TextKor: “누군가 있다. 창문의 뽁뽁이 때문에 얼굴이 흐려져보이지만 얼굴은 확실히 이쪽을 바라보고 있다.”
TextEng: “Someone's there. It's blurry because of the bubble wrap on the window, but they're surely facing this way. ”

TextKor: “저 사람은 아직 당신이 눈치챘다는 걸 모르는 것 같다.”
TextEng: “It looks like they don't know you noticed yet... ”

TextKor: “마음 같아서야 그렇게 하고 싶지만, 창문을 열려고 시도하지는 않고 있다.”
TextEng: “As much as you want to, they're not trying to pry open the window from outside. ”

TextKor: “주거침입을 시도하지 않은 상태에서 섣불리 행동했다가는 경찰 쪽에서 도리어 저 사람 편을 들어줄지도 모른다.”
TextEng: “If you took action while they weren't attempting to break in, the police might stand on their side instead. ”

TextKor: “또한 당신은 이 방의 바닥이 복도의 바닥보다 올라와 있는 점을 눈치챘다. ”
TextEng: “You also noticed the floor of this room is a bit higher up than the floor of the corridor. ”

TextKor: “화장실 창문조차 높은 곳에 있는데도 사람의 머리가 보인다는 건,”
TextEng: “The fact that their head is visible from a higher surface could indicate they stepped onto something, ”

TextKor: “저 사람이 뭔가 밟고 올라와 보고 있을 수도 있지만 키가 엄청 큰 걸 수도 있다.”
TextEng: “or it could simply mean they are extremely tall.“”

TextKor: “덩치가 크다면 먼저 자극했다가 무슨 일이 생길지 모른다.”
TextEng: “If they're tall, you don't know what'll happen once you provoke them. ”

TextKor: “아니, 덩치가 크지 않더라도 과연 맨손이라고 보장할 수 있나?”
TextEng: “Even if they're not as big, how can you be sure they're empty handed? ”

TextKor: “어느 쪽이든 창문을 여는 건 좋은 생각이 아니다.”
TextEng: “Either way, opening the window is a terrible idea. ”

TextKor: “확실하게 잡으려면 조용히 스마트폰을 집어와 사진을 찍어두는 편이 좋을 것이다.”
TextEng: “The only way to catch them red handed is to grab your phone and quietly take a picture to make an evidence. ”
“...As you stood there pondering what to do, the person walked away.”

TextKor: “하필 CCTV는 내일 설치되어 증거라 할 만한 것이 없다.”
TextEng: “What's worse is that the building still doesn't have a security cam, as it'll be installed tomorrow. ”
“They said they'll take patrols more frequently. ”

TextKor: “당신은 딱히 안심되지는 않았지만, 신고를 안 하는 것보다는 낫다고 생각했다.”
TextEng: “You don't feel any safer, but it's better than nothing. ”

TextKor: “당신은 조용히 밖으로 나와 112로 신고 문자를 보냈다.”
TextEng: “You quietly got out of the bathroom to text the police. ”

TextKor: “하지만 사진으로 증거를 남기려던 순간 남자가 사라졌다.”
TextEng: “But as soon as you were about to take a picture of them, they were gone. ”
“We can't just send him to jail for watching someone. ”

TextKor: “아무것도 안 하고 그냥 서있었다면 주거침입으로도 인정이 안 돼요.”
TextEng: “If they were merely standing there not doing anything else, that's not a home invasion. ”
“We can't really do anything for you. ”
“But we'll make sure to take patrol more frequently, just in case. ”

TextKor: “당신은 어제 분리수거를 하고 돌아온 후 물건이 움직인 것 같다는 느낌을 받았다.”
TextEng: “You had this weird feeling that some of the objects were misplaced after you got back from recycling. ”

TextKor: “평소라면 무시했겠지만 꺼림칙한 기분을 떨쳐낼 수 없다.”
TextEng: “You'd usually pass it off as your imagination, but it's hard to ignore this gut-wrenching dread.”

TextKor: “나가기 전에 사진을 찍어두는 게 좋을 것이다.”
TextEng: “It'd be best to take a picture of your room before you leave. ”
“Do you perhaps sell those cleaning kits for electric device?”
“Oh, maybe they have those in Dollar Free? ”

TextKor: “혹시 다있어는 여… 약도 어디쯤에 있는교? 내가 눈이 침침해가지구…”
TextEng: “Where's the uh, the Dollar Free in this map? I have a hard time reading small letters... ”
“You pointed to his current location and politely told him how to get there. ”

TextKor: “아유, 고마워. 혼자 사니까 물어볼 데도 없어서…”
TextEng: “Aw, thank you, child. It's hard to ask people nowadays, especially since I live alone now...”
“Oh, hold on a second, lemme do something for you. ”
“The old man hands you some bucks. ”
“Oh, don't be like that. You remind me of my granddaughter, take the allowance. ”

TextKor: “내가 요새 명절에 아들이나 딸이나 다 바빠서 손주들도 못 본지 꽤 됐어.”
TextEng: “It's been a while since I'd seen my family, since they're all busy during the holidays. ”

TextKor: “유일한 낙이 용돈 주는 거였는데 만나지도 못 하고…”
TextEng: “The only joy in my life was giving my grandchildren allowance, but now they can't even come meet their grandpa...”
“The old man puts crinkled bills in your hands. ”
“You pulled out the picture you took in the morning. ”

TextKor: “공동현관에 CCTV가 생겼으니 누구든 들어왔다면 찍혔을 것이다.”
TextEng: “Now that the entrance has a security cam, if anyone suspicious passed by, they should be recorded. ”
“You want me to check the security cam? What for? ”
“Oh, my! Is that so? Okay, hold on. ”

TextKor: “음… 6시에서 7시 사이에 나간 사람은 좀 있는데, 그 이후로는 아무도 안 지나다녔어.”
TextEng: “Well... Some people went out between 6 to 7 in the morning, but noone's passed by since then. ”

TextKor: “공동현관으로 지나간 게 아니라면 창문으로 들어왔을 수도 있겠네.”
TextEng: “If they didn't come through the entrance, they may have used the window. ”

TextKor: “학생, 이건 경찰에 신고하는 게 나을 거 같아.”
TextEng: “Honey, I think you should call the cops on this one. ”

TextKor: “그래, 일단 끊을 테니까 이따 영상 필요하면 연락해.”
TextEng: “Okay, tell me if you need the footage. I'll hang up for now. ”
“Unfortunately, there are no signs of forced entry, neither at the window nor at the door.”
“We'll fingerprint the items that were moved, ”

TextKor: “흔적을 거의 남기지 않는 걸 보면 장갑을 썼을 수도 있어요…”
TextEng: “but considering they hardly left any trace, they might have used gloves...”
“We reccommend you change the password on your door. ”

TextKor: “침입 흔적이 없다는 점에서 보아, 범인이 비밀번호를 누르고 들어왔을 수도 있거든요.”
TextEng: “If there's no clues left in the room, it's possible they know what your password is. ”

TextKor: “0000처럼 반복되는 번호나 1234처럼 서로 이어지는 번호는 물론이고, 특정 날짜도 비밀번호로 쓰지 마세요.”
TextEng: “Don't use repetitive or continuous code like 0000 or 1234. Refrain from using specific dates, too. ”

TextKor: “또한, 밀가루 같은 게 붙더라도 지문이 보이지 않도록 자주 닦아주세요.”
TextEng: “Also, wipe the buttons on the door lock so powder-like substances don't stick to your fingerprints.”

TextKor: “복도에 CCTV가 없어서 잡기가 힘들겠지만… 순찰을 강화하겠습니다.”
TextEng: “It'd be difficult to put them to justice because the corridor doesn't have any security cameras... we'll enhance the patrol. ”
“If this happens again, please report to us. ”
“Aah, thank you for helping me out last time. ”
“I bought the cleaning kit thanks to you. ”

TextKor: “허허, 쑥스러워하지 말게나. 이 음료수 하나는 학생이 먹게.”
TextEng: “Hoho, a humble person you are. Please, take this drink as a token of appreciation. ”

TextKor: “이 동네는 위험해… 혹시 이상한 놈과 마주친다면 쓰게.”
TextEng: “It's never safe to live in this area; use it wisely. ”
“It seems there's an ex-convict in town whose information has been disclosed.”
“Memorize what he looks like, and use the spray if he tries anything funny. ”

TextKor: “[페퍼 스프레이 같은 아이템은 자동으로 사용할 수 있습니다. ]”
TextEng: “[Items like pepper spray can be used automatically.]”
“It's the same kind you've seen before. ”
“The unfamiliar woman disappeared outside the building.”
“There are red beans scattered on the floor. ”
“You know who I am, don't you. ”
“I heard your alarm blasting off from a mile away. ”
“What the f**k did I even do to deserve this, huh?”

TextKor: “먼저 친 놈이 알아서 자빠져 죽은 게 내 탓이냐?”
TextEng: “It was his fault for accidentally hitting his head too hard on the floor, why do people blame me for his death? ”
“Don't you dare give me that look, you c***. ”

TextKor: “깜빵도 몇 번 가다보면 익숙해지던데 왜, 네 얼굴도 찢어줘?!”
TextEng: “I'd already gone to jail a few times, what's another 2 years? How about I shred YOUR face too, huh? ”
“You missed a little bit, but it worked. ”
“I, I promise I'll kill you soon. ”
“I'll go after him, you call the police! ”

TextKor: “…이후 경찰이 도착했지만, 퇴근 할 때까지 잡혔다는 말은 못 들었다. ”
TextEng: “...The police arrived, but you didn't hear anything about the convict even after you got off work. ”

TextKor: “그… 죄송해요. 놓쳐버렸어요. 제가 조금만 더 빨랐어도…”
TextEng: “I... sorry. I lost him. If I were just a teansy bit quicker... ”

TextKor: “그래도 아마 조만간 잡힐 거예요. 저도 증언할거고요.”
TextEng: “But I'm sure the police will take care of him. I'll give my own testimony as well. ”
“Are you planning to work tomorrow as well? ”
“Who knows when he'll come by again? ”
“Say, can you keep this just to be sure? ”
“He passes you a small note with his phone number scribbled on it.”

TextKor: “저는 이 근처 원룸에 살고 있으니까, 경찰을 부른 후에도 불안하시면 연락하세요.”
TextEng: “I live in one of the buildings close to the store. If you feel unsafe after calling the cops, contact me. ”
“I'll bring a baseball bat with me or something. ”
“You're afraid of running into the criminal again. ”

TextKor: “하지만 저 남자를 이 일에 끌어들이는 것이 과연 좋은 생각인가? ”
TextEng: “But you're not sure if getting him involved is a good idea. ”

TextKor: “다음엔 코피 정도로 끝나지 않을 수 있다. ”
TextEng: “The man might get worse injuries than just a nosebleed. ”
“What would you like to do with the note? ”

TextKor: “당신은 남을 도와주려다 살해당한 사람들의 기사를 본 적이 있다.”
TextEng: “You remember reading several news articles of people who died trying to help others out. ”

TextKor: “그런 일이 일어나지 않기를 바라며 쪽지를 버렸다.”
TextEng: “You throw the note into the trash can, hoping that doesn't happen to the man. ”
“You think 2 against 1 is still going to be safer than 1 against 1. ”
“You saved his number on your phone. ”

TextKor: “음. 들락날락한 사람은 좀 있는데, 다 세입자야. 딱히 수상한 사람은 없어.”
TextEng: “Well, there were some people that went through the entrance, but they're all tenants. I don't see any strangers. ”

TextKor: “이 CCTV로는 드나드는 사람 밖에 못 봐. 학생 방으로 갔는지는 모르겠는 걸. ”
TextEng: “I can only see people passing by the door with this security cam, so I can't see who went to your room. ”

TextKor: “혹시 보고 싶으면 영상 보내주구. 어떡해, 보내줄까?”
TextEng: “If you want to see for yourself, I can send you the footage. What do you say? You want it? ”
“It's giving off bad omen. You have no idea what this means. ”
“Is it to keep something in your room? ”
“Or is it to call something in? ”
“You take all the talisman off the door, as cleanly as possible. ”
“You have a feeling you'll get a goodnight sleep. ”
“You decided to leave the talisman as is and headed inside. ”
“Your throat dries up and every breath you take scratches your lungs. ”

TextKor: “집 안에서도, 밖에서도 안전하지 못하다. 달리 갈 수 있는 곳도 없다.”
TextEng: “You're not safe not only outside, but inside as well. You have nowhere else to go, too. ”
“Even if you call the cops, what difference will it make? ”

TextKor: “당신은 침대 위의 옷을 전부 수납장으로 던져 넣었다.”
TextEng: “You threw all the clothes on the bed into the drawer. ”
“You stood frozen, staring at the bed for a while. ”
“It's your neighbor. You're being too loud. ”
“I'm here to ask you to be a bit more quiet. ”
“It looks like you went home safely. ”
“Wait, are you going to work right now?”
“Um... did you perhaps save my number?”

TextKor: “저, 여기 사신지 얼마나 되신지는 모르겠지만…아니, 이미 아실 것 같지만. ”
TextEng: “Uh, I don't know how long you've been around here, but... no, I'm pretty sure you already know by now. ”
“This town isn't exactly the best place to live in. ”

TextKor: “그러니까 불안하시면 아침도 괜찮으니까 언제든 도와달라고 하세요.”
TextEng: “So if you want help, you can call me any time, even in the mornings. ”

TextKor: “괜찮아? 어제 오후 직원 한테 들었어. 웬 미친놈이 난리쳤다며.”
TextEng: “Are you alright? I heard from the afternoon staff that some guy straight up assaulted you. ”

TextKor: “그런 일이 있었으면 말을 하지 바로 출근했어?”
TextEng: “You should've told me instead of coming into work today, why didn't you tell me? ”

TextKor: “오늘은 돌아가서 쉬는 게 좋을 거 같은데. 남은 근무는 내가 할게, OO씨는 돌아가.”
TextEng: “I think it's best for you to go home and rest. I'll take care of the rest of your shift today, you should go. ”

TextKor: “응? 집에 있는 것도 불안하다는 게 무슨 말이야?”
TextEng: “What? What do you mean staying home scares you more? ”
“Well I'll stay here anyways for the next three hours. ”

TextKor: “겨우 2주 본 사이에 이런 말 하긴 좀 그렇지만…”
TextEng: “I know this might sound a bit strange, especially considering we've only known each other for two weeks, but...”

TextKor: “정 집에 있기 힘들면, 와이프랑 딸한테 물어볼 테니까 내 집으로 가있어도 된다.”
TextEng: “If you're too scared to be anywhere, I can ask my family to let you stay over at our house. ”
“Alright, then. Just tell me if you change your mind at some point. ”

TextKor: “나는 진짜 잠깐만 창고 정리하고 있을 테니, 혹시라도 그새 그 놈 오면 소리 질러라.”
TextEng: “I need to rearrange something in the back real quick, so if that guy comes in again, scream as loud as you can. ”

TextKor: “카운터에 올려진 검은 봉지 안에는 알밤이 잔뜩 들어있다.”
TextEng: “The plastic bag the customer put down on the counter is full of chestnuts. ”
“These... I put a lot of effort into gathering these from the mountains. ”

TextKor: “이거 한 2KG 정도 될 테니까 15,000원 정도 하거든?”
TextEng: “This should come to around 2 kilograms, worth about 11 bucks. ”

TextKor: “술이랑 바꾸게 적당한 가격대 술로 좀 집어와봐라.”
TextEng: “Bring me some drinks that cost as much as that, and we exchange. Deal? ”
“I don't think you know who you're talking to here. I'm friends with the owner of this place, you see. ”
“So you'd better move it before I call them and get you fired. ”
“I'm the manager here but I've never seen you in my life. Who are you? ”
“N-no, no, not the manager, I meant the CEO. ”
“I'm friends with the CEO of this brand, the store, pal. ”
“Then you must know the number, correct? ”

TextKor: “그럼 전화 한 통만 해주실 수 있나요?”
TextEng: “Can you give them a call right now, then? ”

TextKor: “손님은 아니시겠지만, 예전에 다른 분이 사장님 친구를 사칭하신 적이 있거든요. ”
TextEng: “I'm sure you have no bad intentions, no, not at all -- but there was this one time where a customer lied about being friends with the CEO. ”
“They attempted to get a refund for something they didn't buy here. ”

TextKor: “그 분 때문에 손님을 의심하긴 싫지만 사장님께서 당부하셨거든요.”
TextEng: “We'd rather not suspect customers because of that person, ”

TextKor: “지인이라고 하시는 분은 진짜 친구가 맞는지 꼬옥~ 확인하라고요.”
TextEng: “but the boss insisted that we verify whether customers are telling the truth or not. ”

TextKor: “이 사람이 지금…! 당연히 친구지! 내가 그 놈하고 여기, 그, 뭐야. 학교도 나왔어!”
TextEng: “Why, you...! Of COURSE we're friends! We, uh, went to the uh, the same school here! ”
“Oh? You mean the [   ] high school nearby? ”
“Ugh. I knew he was up to no good. ”
“...Hey, are you okay? You look a bit pale. ”

TextKor: “당신은 혹시 모르니 여자가 사라질 때까지 밖에서 기다려본다.”
TextEng: “You decide to wait out until she leaves, in case she tries anything funny. ”

TextKor: “당신은 여자가 다른 곳으로 갈 낌새가 보이지 않아 경찰에 신고했으나, 경찰이 도착했을 때는 여자가 사라져 있었다.”
TextEng: “As soon as you concluded she wasn't going anywhere and called the cops, she disappeared. ”

TextKor: “전부터 별 거 아닌 일로 자꾸 전화하시던데, ”
TextEng: “You've been calling about trivial matters repeatedly; I suggest you quit that. ”

TextKor: “허위 신고는 경범죄 처벌법 위반 혐의로 심판받을 수 있으니 자제하세요.”
TextEng: “You will be charged with punishment of minor offenses act if you keep making false reports. ”

TextKor: “왠지 몸이 으슬으슬하다. 몸살에 걸린 것 같다.”
TextEng: “Your body aches all over; maybe you caught a cold. ”
